{
  "texts": [
    "The time series are first decomposed into three sub-series: trend ( T t), seasonal ( S t), and residual ( R t) using STL.",
    "Subsequently, these three sub-series, concatenated with time features, are separately processed by an encoder architecture with the 2DTCDN block.",
    "Next, the processed sub-series are concatenated to form the input data of the next decoder architecture.",
    "Finally, outcomes of the decoder layer concatenated with time features are delivered to a dense layer to generate the predictions.",
    "Objective functionThe squared error is a loss function frequently employed in time series prediction tasks."
  ]
}